<p>I have written a query to fetch matching name of the person who has <code>domainSkill</code> name = "Retail" and <code>duration &gt; 7</code>.</p>  <p>I tried below codes and they give me <code>Charlie</code> and <code>Jack</code> documents but should give just <code>Jack</code>.</p>  <p><strong>My JSON data:</strong> </p>  <pre><code>        {           "_id" : ObjectId("55c331391f7f8c754b98a996"),           "Name" : "Charlie",           "currentLocation" : "Sunnyvale",           "domainSkills" : [{               "_id" : ObjectId("560ed953b6158a2866d59676"),               "name" : "Retail",               "duration" : "5",             }, {               "_id" : ObjectId("560ed953b6158a2866d59676"),               "name" : "BFSI",               "duration" : "5",             }]         }         {           "_id" : ObjectId("55c331391f7f8c754b98a997"),           "Name" : "Jack",           "currentLocation" : "Sunnyvale",           "domainSkills" : [{               "_id" : ObjectId("560ed953b6158a2866d59677"),               "name" : "Retail",               "duration" : "8",             }, {               "_id" : ObjectId("560ed953b6158a2866d59677"),               "name" : "BFSI",               "duration" : "5",             }]         } </code></pre>  <p><strong>Spring Data MongoDB Queries:</strong></p>  <pre><code>        //Option 1 -Using andOperator         Criteria.where("domainSkills.name")         .andOperator(Criteria.where("domainSkills.duration").gte("7")));          //Option 2 - Using andOperator          Criteria.where("domainSkills.name").exists(true)         .andOperator(             Criteria.where("domainSkills.name"),             Criteria.where("domainSkills.duration").gte(7))         );          //Option 3 - Using andOperator          Criteria.where("domainSkills").exists(true)         .andOperator(             Criteria.where("domainSkills.name"),             Criteria.where("domainSkills.duration").gte(7))         ); </code></pre>